text.tspan: Daily confirmed COVID-19 cases, rolling 7-day average
The number of confirmed cases is lower than the number of total cases. The main reason for this is limited testing.
Source: Johns Hopkins University CSSE COVID-19 Data Last updated 1 July, 15:03 (London time)
Note: The rolling average is the average across seven days the confirmed cases on the particular date, and the previous six days. For
example, the value for 27th March is the average over the 21st to 27th March.
